{% macro day(num) %}
  {% set days = collections.advent2022 %}
  <li class="acalendar__day" {% if days[num - 1].data.active %}data-day="{{ num }}"{% endif %} {% if num === 24 %}style="grid-column: span 2"{% endif %}>
    <div>
      <span aria-hidden="true">{{ num }}</span><a {% if days[num - 1].data.active %}href="/adventcalendar/2022/{{ num }}"{% endif %}>{{ num }}</a>
    </div>
  </li>
{% endmacro %}

<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=UnifrakturCook:wght@700&display=swap&text=1234567890" rel="stylesheet"> 


<h1>{{ title }}</h1>

{% macro day(num) %}
  {% set days = collections.advent2023 %}
  {% set day = days[num - 1] %}
  <li>
    <a href="{{ day.url }}">
      {{ day.data.title | safe  }}
    </a>
  </li>
{% endmacro %}

<ol>
  {{ day(1) }}
  {{ day(2) }}
  {{ day(3) }}
  {{ day(4) }}
  {# {{ day(5) }} #}
  {# {{ day(6) }} #}
  {# {{ day(7) }} #}
  {# {{ day(8) }} #}
  {# {{ day(9) }} #}
  {# {{ day(10) }} #}
</ol>

<p>
  Last year, I launched the <strong>HTMHell Advent Calendar</strong>, which was a great success. Twenty-four authors worldwide contributed fantastic articles on security, accessibility, UX, and performance. The feedback was phenomenal. That's why we're back this year with 24 new blog posts.
</p>

<p>
  I'll publish them one by one every day starting December 1st.<br> In the meantime, you can check out last year's posts or the first unofficial calendar, which only links to existing articles on other sites.
</p>

